- That's a good idea, we haven't tried it yet.
Here is another challenge that we will have to struggle with for a long time, how to make a person physically located in a very small space believe that he is going to an open space, almost endless. We are also working on the idea of treadmills (not like those of gyms), mobile platforms, as well as that of giant balloons.
For now, cheating the brain is not so easy, you still have to work for many years.
That’s what makes working with virtual reality appealing to researchers, who find many things in a state of total conception.
