His speech was addressed to all the people, especially the Christian Copts, the liberals, the enlightened Muslims and the seculars.
All of them, so far undoubtedly in a confused opposition, are afraid.
Fear of a theocracy on the banks of the Nile by the grace of the powerful Muslim community.
As Mohammed Mursi explains, almost apologizing, he has had to temporarily annul the powers of the Constitutional Court and expand his powers “in order to save the revolution.”
However, neither the Egyptians nor the entire world know very well what this 61-year-old engineer with a doctoral degree awarded by the University of Southern California really wants to save.
Do you intend to deprive the judiciary of its power?
In fact, the 234 articles, whose approval has been forced by a constituent assembly composed of 100 predominantly Islamist members at a 15-hour evening meeting, are truly troubling.
As in previous constitutions, the draft also says that the jurisprudence is based on the "principles of Islamic law".
But what does that mean by “principles”?
This was and still is open to interpretation and it seems that Islamists are going to take advantage of this vague formulation, as well as the legal room for manoeuvre that comes with it, to impose a stricter interpretation of sharia law.
